Wear insect repellent outside and dump standing water around your home. Find out more:  https://t.co/sCa4iJB0jj  https://t.co/MNhqzgVgdX

name: Allen County Health
tweet: We need all our Allen County neighbors to get vaccinated if they are eligible and wear masks in public indoor settings for hopefully for just a little while during this high rate of spread so we can finally beat COVID-19 once and for all!

name: Allen County Health
tweet: You've done the right things! This just adds a layer to keep this extra contagious variant from spreading to someone not yet able to get a shot (think kiddos under 12) or those vaccinated without the robust immunity most get (think our oldest friends or those battling cancer).

name: Allen County Health
tweet: Fully vaccinated are still very protected against severe symptoms, hospitalization & death. Wearing a mask in crowded indoor settings is an extra precaution to prevent further spread while we work to get more folks vaccinated.

name: Allen County Health
tweet: All COVID vaccines are still very effective against the new delta variant. But some studies are showing even the fully vaccinated can still get and spread this highly contagious COVID variant to others, which is why the change was made to masking recommendations.
